[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      134[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **AWS Lambda for ingestion orchestration and interaction queries.** The ingestion pipeline (parse sources, normalize, load to Neptune) runs on a schedule (weekly for most sources). Individual Lambda functions handle each source's parsing logic. For the query path, Lambda functions behind API Gateway translate clinical queries ("check these 5 drugs for interactions") into graph traversals, execute them against Neptune, score the results, and return structured responses. The stateless nature of Lambda fits both workloads. Because VPC-attached Lambda functions incur additional cold start latency (ENI creation, 1-5 seconds), configure Provisioned Concurrency (minimum 2-5 instances) on the interaction-engine Lambda to eliminate cold starts on the clinical query path. Alternatively, use a scheduled CloudWatch Events rule to keep the function warm during clinical operating hours.
